The paper deals with the problem of discovering novel classes in an image collection given labelled examples of other classes, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method that involves training a model using both labelled and unlabelled data, which is a common approach in machine learning. This suggests that the paper could also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on standard classification benchmarks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
